  "description": [
    "JUST CHILDREN Drawings by John R Neill By W B WILSON Secretary of Labor CHILD labor is not a new development in the United States but an inheritance from England although the apprentice ships of the seventeenth century where the children served in close association with their masters are not comparable to the present day factory system with its minute division of labor and the steady tension of deadeningly monotonous toil Yet they serve as a link with the factory system and explain why children were put to work in factories where they could become more quickly re munerative to parents and guardians than under the old system At the time no one could foresee the import of transferring the in dustrial work of children from the house to the factor nor was it to be expected that an agricultural and rural population would fore see the evil results the new machine technic would produce The change of front toward the employ ment of children in factories in the nine teenth century was necessarily slow The traditions existing before the Revolution could not be changed suddenly or without knowledge of the new evils The protectionists had not only the best"
  ],
